⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Mirror & the Mark
node AHX · AHX · ⟦The Mirror & the Mark:AHX:c10e51⟧

WHO   — The Mirror & the Mark — the tattoo he comes to reject
WHAT  — The rejection made physical: the iconography the film condemns, framed as a thing the character can no longer stand to wear.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's anti-hate stance is literalized in Derek's revulsion at his own old mark.
HOW   — By holding the camera on the symbol only as the thing Derek now recoils from — never as decoration.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the mark he carved into himself for the cause. The film shows me only so you can watch him learn to hate me.

